         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Sandhurst ¶ 22 Sept 1887 ¶ My dear Baron von Mueller, ¶  ¶ Dr Atkinson, ¶  who has a large property on the Terrick plains, tells me that the inclosed plant has been spreading rapidly and that the stoc...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.09.22</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Paul MacGillivray</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Calocephalus</seg>?, now listed in AVA simply to family Asteraceae (MEL 543224) (accessed 26 April 2023). MS annotation by M: 'Asw 24/9/87'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Sandhurst<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Now Bendigo, Vic.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">22 Sept 1887</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Dr Atkinson,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">H. L Atkinson.</p>
               </note> who has a large property on the Terrick plains, tells me that the inclosed plant has been spreading rapidly and that the stock will not touch it. He is anxious to know its name, whether it is injurious and if it is likely to spread still more or will die out like the thistles. Probably in the absence of flowers or fruit it may be impossible to tell exactly what it is, but I shall be glad of any information you can give me. I suppose it is one of the common composites.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Believe me</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>very truly your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>P H MacGillivray</p>
         </div>
      </body>
